name: survivability-armor-ballistic-laboratory-sabl
notes: The SABL provides independent analysis, ballistic testing, data collection, data reduction and qualification of current and advanced armors.  Capabilities:  The SABL provides the ability to launch a wide range of foreign small arms, kinetic energy threats (up to 30 mm), fragment simulating projectiles (FSP) and ballistic weld projectiles at test-specific velocities. The lab is used to conduct 2,352 Army Tank Purchase Description (ATPD), First-Article Testing (FAT), Production Control Testing (PCT) and to support government and customer-directed research in armor development. This team also conducts failure analysis with use of a high-speed video capture system up to 60,000 feet per second, 10 microseconds rendering and a flash X-ray system. Existing equipment includes an Environmental Conditioning Chamber, full machine shop, a welding lab, flash X-ray and high-speed video.  Benefits:  &#8226;&#8194; Increases crew survivability due to a standard benchmark that all transparent armor is measured against. &#8226;&#8194; Reduces transparent armor acquisition costs due to more competition. &#8226;&#8194; Improves consistent ballistic performance. &#8226;&#8194; Reduces life-cycle costs. &#8226;&#8194; International Organization for Standardization (ISO) 17025 accredited.
title: Survivability Armor Ballistic Laboratory (SABL)
